<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Opulent" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Opulent,</orth> rich, plenteous, ample: <cit><quote>to draw a third more o. than your sisters,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will piece her o. throne with kingdoms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 5, 46</bibl></cit>.
